cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the use of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) in 5G networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), system design (cs.SY), multimedia communication (cs.MM), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, since the paper focuses more on the technical aspects of NOMA and its applications in 5G networks, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories.
